pageContext.claim: “Pfizer and others even decided to not assess the results of their vaccine; in other words, not come out with a vaccine until just after the election. That's because of what I did with favored nations and these other elements, instead of their original plan to assess the data in October. So they were going to come out in October, but they decided to delay it because of what I'm doing.....so they waited and waited and waited. And they thought they'd come out with it a few days after the election.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump baselessly accused both Pfizer and the Food and Drug Administration of intentionally withholding news that its coronavirus vaccine candidate is more than 90 percent effective until after the presidential election, even though Pfizer did not have access to the data until the Sunday after the election.
